{{Jainism}}
'''Antakrddaaśāh''' is the eighth of the 12 [[Jain]] āgamas said to be promulgated by [[Mahavira|Māhavīra]] himself. Antakrddaaśāh  translated as "Ten Chapters on End-Makers" is said to have been composed by [[Ganadhara]] [[Sudharmaswami]] as per the [[Svetambara|Śvetámbara]] tradition.

It contains stories describing those who succeeded in destroying all their [[Karma in Jainism|karmas]] and succeeded in attaining Moksa and putting an end to the re-births.

